<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-16764] New consumer should throw InvalidTopicException on poll when invalid topic in metadata</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-16764</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A call to consumer.poll should throw InvalidTopicException if an invalid topic is discovered in metadata. This can be easily reproduced by calling subscribe(&quot;invalid topic&quot;) and then poll, for example.The new consumer does not throw the expected InvalidTopicException like the LegacyKafkaConsumer does. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The legacy consumer achieves this by checking for metadata exceptions on every iteration of the ConsumerNetworkClient (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/0e023e1f736ea03568032cc282803df8e61eb451/clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerNetworkClient.java#L315&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is probably what makes that &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/0e023e1f736ea03568032cc282803df8e61eb451/clients/src/test/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/KafkaConsumerTest.java#L2956&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;testSubscriptionOnInvalidTopic&lt;/a&gt; fails for the new consumer. Once this bug is fixed, we should be able to enable that test for the new consumer.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
